<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1374,1507]" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1300284274" country="Liberia" location="Afrotropical region" municipality="Oriental region" pageId="14" pageNumber="537" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="South">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[278,374,1374,1398]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Javalbia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[278,374,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Javalbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed and is known from the Oriental, Palaearctic and Afrotropical regions. Especially rich in species is the 
<collectingMunicipality box="[510,683,1410,1435]" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Oriental region</collectingMunicipality>
, with 20 species described (
<bibRefCitation author="Smit" pageId="14" pageNumber="537" refString="Smit, H. &amp; Pesic V. (2014) Water mites from Mount Kinabalu and the Crocker Range, Borneo, Malaysia (Acari: Hydrachnidia), withn the description of 34 new species. Zootaxa, 3876 (1), 1 - 71. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3876.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Smit &amp; Pešić 2014, Smit in prep, Pešić &amp; Smit in prep</bibRefCitation>
). From the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:92673E50FFC0350CC3ED550FFBE273E4:1F11D99DFFC0350CC2B855B1FD0973B8" box="[450,666,1446,1471]" country="Liberia" municipality="Oriental region" name="Afrotropical region" pageId="14" pageNumber="537" stateProvince="South">Afrotropical region</location>
only two species have been described, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook, 1966" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1966" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Javalbia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana" subGenus="Javalbiopsis">
<emphasis box="[1149,1436,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">J. (Javalbiopsis) africana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[151,282,1482,1507]" pageId="14" pageNumber="537" refString="Cook, D. R. (1966) The water mites of Liberia. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 6, 1 - 418." type="journal article" year="1966">Cook, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[350,431,1482,1507]" name="Liberia" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Liberia</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="K.O. Viets, 1974" authorityName="K.O. Viets" authorityYear="1974" box="[485,917,1482,1507]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Javalbia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata" subGenus="Javalbiopsis">
<emphasis box="[485,721,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">J. (Javalbiopsis) lata</emphasis>
K.O. Viets, 1974
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[985,1050,1482,1507]" country="Cameroon" name="South" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">South</collectingRegion>
Africa
</materialsCitation>
.
